[audience chuckles]

16:37.900 --> 16:42.033
Now, we're going to fix a value
on this 15 year old trailer.

16:42.100 --> 16:43.533
Not a replacement trailer.

16:43.600 --> 16:45.967
I also added gorilla lifts to it,
on the gate.

16:46.033 --> 16:48.367
-[Judy] You have what?
-Gorilla lifts on the gate.

16:48.433 --> 16:50.734
Do you have a receipt for the trailer?

16:50.800 --> 16:55.000
No, that's... a divorce ago
and many moons ago.

16:55.066 --> 16:56.600
-[Judy] Fifteen years ago.
-Yeah.

16:56.667 --> 16:59.633
Could you find,
not a replacement for the trailer--

16:59.700 --> 17:02.066
-You're talking about a new replacement?
-Mm-hmm.

17:02.133 --> 17:03.834
Well, he's not buying you a new trailer

17:03.900 --> 17:05.667
I'm not asking for a new price, either.

17:05.734 --> 17:09.600
Well, I'm asking you, how do you expect me
to value this 15 year old trailer?

17:09.667 --> 17:13.467
He's clearly responsible for it.
You told the police $2,500.

17:13.533 --> 17:17.200
Now, did he ever tell you
what he paid for that trailer?

17:17.266 --> 17:20.233
-Yes, ma'am.
-Let's start with when did he tell you

17:20.300 --> 17:22.266
how much he paid for the trailer?

17:22.333 --> 17:26.100
After the incident, he told me
he paid $1,500 for it,

17:26.166 --> 17:31.867
and added a gorilla lift that was $300
or $400 or $500, something like that.

17:31.934 --> 17:33.567
But he told me $1,500 on the trailer.

17:33.633 --> 17:36.367
-[Judy] And he added a gorilla lift.
-Yeah, that's what he said.

17:36.433 --> 17:39.400
Where were you when you had
this conversation, on the phone--

17:39.467 --> 17:42.800
It was over the phone.
It was, uh, basically him trying to...

17:42.867 --> 17:45.133
get me to pay for it.

17:45.200 --> 17:47.033
Yes. So, you had this conversation.

17:47.100 --> 17:50.000
You remember speaking to him
about the payment for the trailer?

17:50.066 --> 17:51.333
Oh, we spoke in person, too.

17:51.400 --> 17:53.600
I don't know if we said that
on the phone or in person

17:53.667 --> 17:55.734
Oh, we didn't say that much in person.

17:55.800 --> 17:58.867
Okay, well, so then, I will ask you
this question, Mr. Boydston.

17:58.934 --> 18:03.000
Did you, in fact, tell him
that you paid $1,500 for the trailer?

18:03.066 --> 18:05.000
And then put on gorilla lifts?

18:05.066 --> 18:07.800
-I don't recall saying that, but--
-[Judy] Well, he does.

18:07.867 --> 18:09.767
I don't recall saying that,
but I may have.

18:09.834 --> 18:13.100
Yeah, you may have. I may have.
Well, if you may have...

18:13.166 --> 18:16.700
that suggests to me you wouldn't have
said that if you didn't know that that was

18:16.767 --> 18:19.900
either <i>the </i>price that you paid for it
or the ballpark figure.

18:19.967 --> 18:23.500
Do you remember telling him how much
you paid to have the gorilla lifts put on?

18:23.567 --> 18:25.367
And I don't know what gorilla lifts are.

18:25.433 --> 18:28.033
It's a spring assist on the gate
so it's not so hard to lift.

18:28.100 --> 18:30.033
Okay. Do you remember when you did that?

18:30.100 --> 18:31.333
[Donald]
A couple years ago.

18:31.400 --> 18:33.100
Do you remember how much it cost you?

18:33.166 --> 18:34.300
I think it was $250.

18:34.367 --> 18:37.333
[Judy]
So, $1,500 and $250, is $1,750.

18:37.400 --> 18:40.533
That's what you paid for the trailer.
That's what you told him.

18:40.600 --> 18:42.867
And since you don't remember
and he does remember,

18:42.934 --> 18:46.967
and it could've been, which suggests to me
that it's probably what you said to him,

18:47.033 --> 18:48.767
that's $1,700. Now, do--

18:48.834 --> 18:52.233
The problem with that is, Your Honor,
is you can't replace that for $1,750.

18:52.300 --> 18:55.266
-[Judy] Of course you can't.
-Even used, you can't replace it for that.

18:55.333 --> 18:57.934
-They're going for $2,500 to $3,500.
-I don't know.

18:58.000 --> 19:00.834
I mean, if you buy--
Let's say you bought a ounce of silver,

19:00.900 --> 19:03.033
and the price of silver goes up
to $50 an ounce.

19:03.100 --> 19:05.033
Are you gonna sell it
for what you gave for it,

19:05.100 --> 19:06.967
or are you gonna sell it
for what it's worth?

19:07.033 --> 19:10.033
Well, let me tell you this.
Think about an insurance company.

19:10.100 --> 19:13.300
When you insure your car,
and your car is stolen,

19:13.367 --> 19:17.166
and you paid for your car $100,000,
15 years ago.

19:17.233 --> 19:20.867
And you have both collision and liability.

19:20.934 --> 19:25.600
Do you think that the insurance company
is going to pay you $100,000 for your car,

19:25.667 --> 19:28.467
or are they going to pay you
the current value of the car?

19:28.533 --> 19:30.700
-Well, I understand that, but--
-[laughs]

19:30.767 --> 19:32.400
But the trailers are going up. I mean,

19:32.467 --> 19:34.500
if your car's worth more
than you gave for it--

19:34.567 --> 19:36.633
[Judy]
Oh, if things increase in value, yes.

19:36.700 --> 19:39.200
If you bought a car that
appreciates in value,

19:39.266 --> 19:42.367
then the insurance company would
have to pay the appreciated value.

19:42.433 --> 19:46.066
-But he's not buying you a new trailer.
-Well, I'm not asking for a new trailer.

19:46.133 --> 19:48.500
I'm just asking for a price
that will get me close to where

19:48.567 --> 19:50.667
I can take and add some more
money to it and get--

19:50.734 --> 19:53.600
'Cause if you buy a used one,
chances are you're gonna buy a stolen one.

19:53.667 --> 19:55.633
Well, that's possible.
Maybe you buy your own.

